76561197970840537,Recommended,312230,16915227,"Posted: 6 July, 2015",all,infin,"A short, enjoyable existential space scifi experience that pays homage to the System Shock series and 2001: A Space Odyssey (among others).  The gameplay mechanics are varied but with limited depth:  light exploration, light combat/stealth, light puzzling.  Similarly, the visual aesthetic (and, some might argue, the graphical fidelity) is minimalist; yet smooth and responsive.  The real focus in Spirits of Xanadu is the high quality narrative and its beautiful integration with the simple but immersive game world, aided by strong writing and voice work.That said, I don't know that I can recommend paying for the game at its full price given the extreme briefness of the experience -- even including the multiple replays required to see all the endings.  It's also worth noting that on almost all difficulty levels you will likely face at least a few frustrating/unfair 'deaths'... though at least a couple of these are tied to the narrative.  When on sale, however, the System Shock 2 nostalgia evoked here alone is well worth the (sale) price to me.I'm hoping these developers continue in the vein of Spirits of Xanadu, preferably with larger/deeper game worlds."
