76561198073300109,Recommended,312230,21194826,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,Toni,"Greenlit the game, bought it, played and now I'll recommend it.Despite being short, the game feels very complete, there are many things to interact with and tasks to perform around the spaceship. One very good point is that the game doesn't babysit you, if you want the solution to something that's going on you have to search, look for a tip, think and figure it out by yourself.The FPS part is very simple, not much depth, just a few guns, the basic for you to survive, shoot to kill and don't let them get you (though a ""stealth"" approach is possible to deal with some enemies). There are also different difficulty levels to satisfy your playstyle.But what this game really excells at is it's atmosphere, the mystery, the experiences you'll have, whether you understand them or not. The plot isn't given to you, you have to find out about it, imagine what happened, how it happened and why. All in all,  Spirits of Xanadu is a short but very solid experience. well worth playing.PS: Did I mention there's a zombie shooting mini-game?"
