,Recommended,312230,25074412,"Posted: 22 August, 2016",all,Kaishi,"The atmosphere in this game is pretty fantastic.  Also the writing.  It reminds me of a minimalist version of System Shock meets Dead Space.It's short, sweet, and cohesive.  It feels like a fleshed-out game-jam-type production.  The systems present in the game are well-developed (lighting, basic combat, item placement, mystery) and while other systems could have been implemented, they don't feel missing to me.For example, all weapons have infinite ammo.  This means the devs didn't have to spend time balancing ammo pickups and placement, magazine sizes, overheat meters, etc.  It's an oldschool decision that works well in this environment."
