76561198000318945,Recommended,312230,31345425,Posted: 24 April,all,Trrcn,"I want to begin with noting the length of the game.  This game could easily be completed in fifteen minutes up to an hour if you want to find everything on a blind run.  That being said let's being.In Spirits of Xanadu you control a nameless female space detective on a mission to investigate what happened to the crew of four on the space vessel 'Xanadu'. While on the ship, everything is done in the 1st person perspective almost in the exact way as System Shock. You get two weapons, you figure puzzles to turn on computers, get passcodes to doors, etc.  All the while you shoot at, hack, or escape robots which try to kill you.  Without revealing too much more I'll leave it at that and say it's an eerie and welcome experience for so cheap.Get it if it's under $10.  It'll get your System Shock urges down until the real deal releases from this very same company later in the year."
