,Recommended,312230,21020508,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,dairy farmer,"System Shock with simplified combat, minus RPG elements, boiled down into a 3-4 hour experience.The game has some very obvious System Shock (2) influences -- the layout of the ship, the sound of your footsteps on metal, the select-fire laser pistol, and even the audio log icons pretty much all scream ""System Shock 2"". And despite the game's length, it's also home to a surprising number of other sci-fi game and movie references.As mentioned, there is no real RPG-like progression, and even though you have a weapon, it's almost more of a tool for solving problems (in the form of enemies).The writing is surprisingly competent, as are the puzzles. Even more surprising is the quality of the audio log voiceovers. They're at least on par with SS2, if perhaps even a bit better than some of SS2's voice actors.Graphics aren't exactly impressive, as you can see from the screenshots, but they get the job done and at the very least don't hurt your eyes. I think there could've been improvement on making more obvious what items can be interacted with though, which would've helped with some puzzles.As a warning, this game does contain some moderate atmospheric tension. At times you'll experience some environmental surprises that keep you on edge, but there are no cheap jump-scares, unless perhaps you run around a corner too fast and run into an enemy."
