,Recommended,312230,35492374,Posted: 5 October,all,Twobirds,"The obvious inspiration for Spirits of Xanadu is System Shock 2 - you have a variety of weapons in an FPS style, you're stuck on a lonely space station, crazed robots are after you, you find audio logs, piece together a story, it's spooky but not too spooky, and get the place up and running in order to complete your mission.  It's on the short side but there isn't much filler at all, and the weird moments remain weird and interesting (there are multiple endings, too).The layout of the ship is a little goofy at times, and some enemies tend to be a little annoying, but it's a solid few hours of entertainment if you like the style.  Voice acting was surprisingly solid for an indie game, and there are a lot of little details that make exploring worthwhile."
